  "commentary": "With SPX at 7104.04 sitting just below the max negative gamma strike at 7115, dealers are currently in a position where they need to buy any dips and sell any rallies, creating stabilizing forces around current levels. The PIN regime with 53.2B in total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting behavior, with the massive +7.6B gamma wall at 7200 acting as a significant ceiling where dealer selling pressure will intensify on any push higher. Key levels to watch are 7115 (max negative gamma turning point) and the 7150/7200 double wall of positive gamma that should cap upside momentum.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy trading with resistance capping moves toward 7150-7200.",
